caption.text: STEP 5: Next i choose the "Tune Image" feature in Snapseed. There you can adjust brightness, ambiance, contrast, saturation, and white balance. I usually change these back and forth to their extremes to see if I like what it's doing to the image. If I do, then I'll make the adjustment more subtly. With this photo I first decrease the brightness to subdue the over-saturation (see left frame). Then I shifted the white balance slightly towards red to give everything a little bit of rose hue. My taste in my editing has moved towards more minimalism so at this stage also, I do my best to not over edit. (A couple more steps and we're almost done).
